parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing belt can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs, and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine makes a loud noise
the engine stalls or fails to start
the vehicle experiences a loss of power
the timing belt breaks or snaps.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Difficulty starting the engine, especially in the morning, can be a nuisance and may lead to increased wear on the starter motor and battery.
symptoms: The engine is hard to start
the engine takes multiple attempts to start
the vehicle experiences a delay in starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Repeated failures of the muffler and tailpipe can lead to increased emissions, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially cause safety hazards due to exhaust leaks.
symptoms: The muffler or tailpipe fails prematurely
the vehicle experiences excessive noise from the exhaust system
the vehicle has a decrease in fuel efficiency
the vehicle has an increase in emissions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracks in the fuel tank can cause fuel leakage, which can lead to fires, explosions, and accidents, posing a significant risk to vehicle occupants and other road users.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the seams of the fuel tank
signs of fuel leakage around the fuel tank
cracks visible on the fuel tank
fuel smell or odor inside or outside the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Dual Airbags to Deploy
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of dual airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can increase the risk of serious injury or fatality to the occupants, compromising vehicle safety.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
despite the severity of the impact
occupants experience increased injury or fatality risk.
